On Tue, 12 Apr 2005, Zach Freshman wrote:

> I've checked all the connections at the starter. Ignition switch is less
> than a year old so is starter. I didn't bridge the solenoid connections
> to see if the starter turned cause I didn't think of it at the time. But
> that wouldn't cause my power to kill would it. Later when I tried again,
> it sounded like juice was trying to get to the starter, but couldn't
> Please help diagnose. I'd rather not give Ron another $30 for an
> ignition switch if I don't need too. :)

before doing a new ignition switch, check:

	- battery water levels (charge it too)
	- battery terminals
	- ground strap connection -- wire brush it off

and double check those starter nuts (that hold the wires on).

also: did you replace the starter bushing when you replaced the starter? 
(did you need to?)

	-t
